Imports System Imports System.Data Imports System.Math Imports Microsoft.SqlServer.Dts.Runtime Imports System.Collections.Generic
<Microsoft.SqlServer.Dts.Tasks.ScriptTask.SSISScriptTaskEntryPointAttribute> _ <System.CLSCompliantAttribute(False)> _ Partial Public Class ScriptMain Inherits Microsoft.SqlServer.Dts.Tasks.ScriptTask.VSTARTScriptObjectModelBase
Enum ScriptResults Success = Microsoft.SqlServer.Dts.Runtime.DTSExecResult.Success Failure = Microsoft.SqlServer.Dts.Runtime.DTSExecResult.Failure End Enum
' The execution engine calls this method when the task executes. ' To access the object model, use the Dts property. Connections, variables, events, ' and logging features are available as members of the Dts property as shown in the following examples. ' ' To reference a variable, call Dts.Variables("MyCaseSensitiveVariableName").Value ' To post a log entry, call Dts.Log("This is my log text", 999, Nothing) ' To fire an event, call Dts.Events.FireInformation(99, "test", "hit the help message", "", 0, True) ' ' To use the connections collection use something like the following: ' ConnectionManager cm = Dts.Connections.Add("OLEDB") ' cm.ConnectionString = "Data Source=localhost;Initial Catalog=AdventureWorks;Provider=SQLNCLI10;Integrated Security=SSPI;Auto Translate=False;" ' ' Before returning from this method, set the value of Dts.TaskResult to indicate success or failure. ' ' To open Help, press F1. Public Sub iterateOutputvars(ByRef procreturn As Integer, ByRef runid As Nullable(Of Integer), ByRef status As String) For Each var In Dts.Variables If var.Name.Contains("procreturn") Then var.Value = procreturn Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("runid") And runid.HasValue Then var.Value = runid Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("processstatus") Then var.Value = status Continue For End If Next
End Sub Public Sub iterateInputvars(ByRef orchestrationschema As String, _ ByRef myprocessname As String, _ ByRef orchestrationDBconnection As String, _ ByRef operationtype As String, _ ByRef taskname As String, _ ByRef statusvalue As List(Of String), _ ByRef commandtimeoutval As Integer, _ ByRef goodflag As Nullable(Of Integer)) For Each var In Dts.Variables If var.Name.Contains("schema") Then orchestrationschema = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("goodflag") Then goodflag = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("TaskName") Then taskname = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("operationtype") Then operationtype = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("processname") Then myprocessname = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("statusvalue") Then statusvalue.Add(var.Value) Continue For End If If var.Value.ToString().Contains("SQLNCLI") Then orchestrationDBconnection = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("commandtimeoutval") Then commandtimeoutval = var.Value Continue For End If
Next
End Sub
Public Sub Main() ' ' Add your code here ' Dim apiname As String = "usp_get_process_run_info" Dim orchestrationschema As String = "" Dim myprocessname As String = "" Dim orchestrationDBconnection As String = "" Dim operationtype As String = "" Dim goodflag As Nullable(Of Integer) = Nothing Dim commandtimeoutval As Integer = 7200
Dim procReturn As Integer Dim runid As Nullable(Of Integer) = Nothing Dim status As String = "" Dim exceptionmsg As String = "" Dim eventid As Integer = 0 Dim taskname As String = "" Dim statusvalue As New List(Of String)
iterateInputvars(orchestrationschema, myprocessname, orchestrationDBconnection, operationtype, taskname, statusvalue, commandtimeoutval, goodflag)
If operationtype = "Manual" Or operationtype = "Exclude" Then Dts.TaskResult = ScriptResults.Success Return ElseIf operationtype = "Automatic" Then
' call function to call orchestration 'callOrch(orchestrationDBconnection, orchestrationschema, apiname, myprocessname, procReturn, status, runid) ' Try usp_get_process_run_info(orchestrationDBconnection, orchestrationschema, myprocessname, goodflag, procReturn, status, runid, exceptionmsg, eventid, commandtimeoutval)
Catch ex As Exception exceptionmsg = "Exception:" + ex.Message.ToString() End Try
If Not statusvalue.Contains(status) Then If exceptionmsg.Length > 0 Then exceptionmsg = exceptionmsg + "; " + status + " of " + myprocessname + " doesnt match expected status value" Else exceptionmsg = status + " status of " + myprocessname + " doesnt match expected status" End If eventid = -997 End If If procReturn <> 0 Then exceptionmsg = exceptionmsg + "; Orchestration returned Invalid returncode" End If Else exceptionmsg = "Invalid operationtype specified" eventid = -1 End If ' assign result to output vars iterateOutputvars(procReturn, runid, status)
Dim emptyBytes(0) As Byte
' if there was an exception, eventid is not zero, status doesnt match expected status, or procReturn is not zero then fail task If exceptionmsg <> "" Or eventid <> 0 Or Not statusvalue.Contains(status) Or procReturn <> 0 Then Dts.Log("Exception msg:" & exceptionmsg, 0, emptyBytes) Dts.Events.FireError(eventid, taskname, exceptionmsg, String.Empty, 0) End If
Dts.TaskResult = ScriptResults.Success
End Sub
Public Sub usp_get_process_run_info(ByVal orchestrationDBconnection As String, _ ByVal orchestrationschema As String, _ ByVal myprocessname As String, _ ByVal goodflag As Nullable(Of Integer), _ ByRef procReturn As Integer, _ ByRef status As String, _ ByRef runID As Nullable(Of Integer), _ ByRef exceptionmsg As String, _ ByRef eventid As Integer, _ Optional ByVal commandTimeoutVal As Integer = 7200) ' add connection info Dim apiname As String = "usp_get_process_run_info" Dim cn As New OleDb.OleDbConnection(orchestrationDBconnection)
Dim nonquerycommand As OleDb.OleDbCommand = cn.CreateCommand() nonquerycommand.CommandType = CommandType.StoredProcedure nonquerycommand.CommandTimeout = commandTimeoutVal
Try 'open connection cn.Open()
'create command text nonquerycommand.CommandText = orchestrationschema + "." + apiname
' add parameters Dim l_procreturn As New OleDb.OleDbParameter l_procreturn = nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.Integer, 8) l_procreturn.Direction = ParameterDirection.ReturnValue
nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 100).Value = myprocessname
Dim l_runid As New OleDb.OleDbParameter l_runid = nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.Integer, 8) l_runid.Direction = ParameterDirection.Output
Dim l_status As OleDb.OleDbParameter l_status = nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 100) l_status.Direction = ParameterDirection.Output
nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.Integer, 8).Value = goodflag
'prepare command for exec nonquerycommand.Prepare()
' call get info from Orchestration nonquerycommand.ExecuteNonQuery()
status = l_status.Value procReturn = l_procreturn.Value If Not IsDBNull(l_runid.Value) AndAlso Integer.TryParse(l_runid.Value, 0) Then runID = l_runid.Value 'Else : runID = 0 End If
Catch ex As OleDb.OleDbException procReturn = -1 status = "" runID = -1 eventid = -995 exceptionmsg = "OLEDB Exception: " + ex.Message.ToString() Catch ex As ArgumentException procReturn = -1 status = "" runID = -1 eventid = -994 exceptionmsg = "Argument Exception: " + ex.Message.ToString() Catch ex As Exception procReturn = -1 status = "" runID = -1 eventid = -1 exceptionmsg = ex.Message.ToString() Finally If cn.State = ConnectionState.Open Then cn.Close() End If
End Try
End Sub
End Class

Public Sub Main() ' ' Add your code here ' Dim apiname As String = "usp_check_dependency" Dim myschema As String = "" Dim myprocessname As String = "" Dim chkdepschema As String = "" Dim chkdepdatabase As String = "" Dim otherprocessname As String = "" Dim waitminute As Integer = 0 Dim intervalminute As Integer = 0 Dim elapsedminute As Integer = 0 Dim orchestrationDBconnection As String = "" Dim operationtype As String = "" Dim exceptionthreshold As Integer = 0 Dim l_exceptionthreshold As Integer = 0 Dim verboseexceptions As Integer = 0 Dim commandtimeoutval As Integer = 7200
' DLL exceptions Dim Exception_OLEDB As Integer = -995 Dim Exception_Argument As Integer = -994 Dim Exception_InvalidCast As Integer = -993 Dim Exception_General As Integer = -1
Dim procReturn As Integer Dim processreturnvalueint As Integer Dim status As String = "Not Ready"
Dim exceptionmsg As String = "" Dim l_exceptionmsg As String = "" Dim agg_exceptionmsg As String = ""
Dim eventid As Integer = 0 Dim taskname As String = ""
iterateInputvars(operationtype, taskname, orchestrationDBconnection, myschema, chkdepdatabase, chkdepschema, myprocessname, otherprocessname, waitminute, intervalminute, exceptionthreshold, verboseexceptions, commandtimeoutval)
If operationtype = "Manual" Or operationtype = "Exclude" Then status = "Ready" Return ' valid wait minute is provided but interval minute is not provided ElseIf waitminute >= 0 And intervalminute <= 0 Then exceptionmsg = Now().ToString + "Exception: Invalid interval minute and wait minute combination provided" ElseIf operationtype <> "Automatic" And operationtype <> "Manual" And operationtype <> "Exclude" Then exceptionmsg = Now().ToString + "Invalid operationtype specified" Else 'operationtype = "Automatic" ' function to call orchestration Try usp_check_dependency(orchestrationDBconnection, myschema, myprocessname, chkdepdatabase, chkdepschema, otherprocessname, -1, 0, procReturn, processreturnvalueint, status, l_exceptionmsg, eventid, commandtimeoutval) Catch ex As Exception l_exceptionthreshold += 1 l_exceptionmsg = ex.Message.ToString() End Try If eventid = Exception_OLEDB Or eventid = Exception_General Then l_exceptionthreshold += 1 End If
'MsgBox("Exit try-Orch output: procReturn: " + procReturn.ToString + " processReturnValueInt: " + processreturnvalueint.ToString + " Status: " + status.ToString + " exceptionmsg: " + exceptionmsg.ToString) ' Capture any invalid process names, myprocess running errors If processreturnvalueint <> 0 Then exceptionmsg = Now().ToString + "Exception: Process/database doesnt exist or myprocess is in running state; " + l_exceptionmsg ElseIf eventid = Exception_Argument Or eventid = Exception_InvalidCast Then exceptionmsg = Now().ToString + "Exception: Argument exception or Invalid cast exception; " + l_exceptionmsg Else While status <> "Ready" And (waitminute = 0 Or (waitminute > 0 And elapsedminute < waitminute)) And (exceptionthreshold = 0 Or (exceptionthreshold > 0 And l_exceptionthreshold < exceptionthreshold)) If verboseexceptions = 1 Then agg_exceptionmsg = agg_exceptionmsg + l_exceptionmsg End If 'convert intervalminute to milliseconds; System.Threading.Thread.Sleep(intervalminute * 60 * 1000)
' call the orchestration engine Try usp_check_dependency(orchestrationDBconnection, myschema, myprocessname, chkdepdatabase, chkdepschema, otherprocessname, -1, 0, procReturn, processreturnvalueint, status, l_exceptionmsg, eventid, commandtimeoutval) Catch ex As Exception l_exceptionthreshold += 1 l_exceptionmsg = ex.Message.ToString() End Try ' increment any oledb exceptions If eventid = Exception_OLEDB Or eventid = Exception_General Then l_exceptionthreshold += 1 End If ' increment elapsedminute elapsedminute = elapsedminute + intervalminute 'MsgBox("Exit try-Orch output: procReturn: " + procReturn.ToString + " processReturnValueInt: " + processreturnvalueint.ToString + " Status: " + status.ToString + " exceptionmsg: " + exceptionmsg.ToString) End While End If
End If
If status = "Ready" Then exceptionmsg = "" eventid = 0 iterateOutputvars(procReturn, processreturnvalueint, status) Else If (waitminute > 0 And elapsedminute >= waitminute) Then If verboseexceptions = 1 Then exceptionmsg = exceptionmsg + agg_exceptionmsg + ";" + Now().ToString + " Time Out - Check dependency is not ready" Else exceptionmsg = exceptionmsg + ";" + Now().ToString + "Time Out - Check dependency is not ready;" End If End If
If (exceptionthreshold > 0 And l_exceptionthreshold > exceptionthreshold) Then If verboseexceptions = 1 Then exceptionmsg = exceptionmsg + agg_exceptionmsg + ";" + Now().ToString + " Exception count exceeds threshold." Else exceptionmsg = exceptionmsg + ";" + Now().ToString + " Exception count exceeds threshold." End If End If eventid = -998 Dim emptyBytes(0) As Byte Dts.Log("Exception msg:" & exceptionmsg, 0, emptyBytes) Dts.Events.FireError(eventid, taskname, exceptionmsg, String.Empty, 0) End If
Dts.TaskResult = ScriptResults.Success End Sub
Public Sub usp_check_dependency(ByVal orchestrationDBconnection As String, _ ByVal orchestrationschema As String, _ ByVal myprocessname As String, _ ByVal chkdep_databasename As String, _ ByVal chkdep_schemaname As String, _ ByVal otherprocessname As String, _ ByVal waitminute As Integer, _ ByVal pollingminute As Integer, _ ByRef procReturn As Integer, _ ByRef processreturnvalueint As Integer, _ ByRef result As String, _ ByRef exceptionmsg As String, _ ByRef eventid As Integer, _ Optional ByVal commandTimeoutVal As Integer = 7200)
' add connection info Dim apiname As String = "usp_check_dependency" Dim cn As New OleDb.OleDbConnection(orchestrationDBconnection)
Dim nonquerycommand As OleDb.OleDbCommand = cn.CreateCommand() nonquerycommand.CommandType = CommandType.StoredProcedure nonquerycommand.CommandTimeout = commandTimeoutVal
Try 'open connection cn.Open()
'create command text nonquerycommand.CommandText = orchestrationschema + "." + apiname
' add parameters Dim l_procreturn As New OleDb.OleDbParameter l_procreturn = nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.Integer, 8) l_procreturn.Direction = ParameterDirection.ReturnValue
nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 500).Value = chkdep_databasename nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 500).Value = chkdep_schemaname nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 500).Value = myprocessname nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 500).Value = otherprocessname nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.Integer, 8).Value = waitminute nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.Integer, 8).Value = pollingminute
Dim l_result As New OleDb.OleDbParameter l_result = nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 255) l_result.Direction = ParameterDirection.Output
Dim l_processreturnvalueint As New OleDb.OleDbParameter l_processreturnvalueint = nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.Integer, 8) l_processreturnvalueint.Direction = ParameterDirection.Output
nonquerycommand.CommandTimeout = 0 'prepare command for exec nonquerycommand.Prepare()
' call get info from Orchestration nonquerycommand.ExecuteNonQuery()
procReturn = l_procreturn.Value result = l_result.Value If Not IsDBNull(l_processreturnvalueint.Value) AndAlso Integer.TryParse(l_processreturnvalueint.Value, 0) Then processreturnvalueint = l_processreturnvalueint.Value Else : processreturnvalueint = -1 End If
Catch ex As OleDb.OleDbException procReturn = -1 processreturnvalueint = -1 eventid = -995 exceptionmsg = "OLEDB Exception: " + ex.Message.ToString() Catch ex As ArgumentException procReturn = -1 processreturnvalueint = -1 eventid = -994 exceptionmsg = "Argument Exception: " + ex.Message.ToString() Catch ex As InvalidCastException procReturn = -1 processreturnvalueint = -1 eventid = -993 exceptionmsg = "Invalid cast Exception: " + ex.Message.ToString() Catch ex As Exception procReturn = -1 processreturnvalueint = -1 eventid = -1 exceptionmsg = ex.Message.ToString() Finally If cn.State = ConnectionState.Open Then cn.Close() End If End Try
End Sub

End Sub Public Sub iterateInputvars(ByRef orchestrationschema As String, _ ByRef myprocessname As String, _ ByRef orchestrationDBconnection As String, _ ByRef operationtype As String, _ ByRef taskname As String, _ ByRef statusvalue As List(Of String), _ ByRef commandtimeoutval As Integer, _ ByRef goodflag As Nullable(Of Integer)) For Each var In Dts.Variables If var.Name.Contains("schema") Then orchestrationschema = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("goodflag") Then goodflag = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("TaskName") Then taskname = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("operationtype") Then operationtype = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("processname") Then myprocessname = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("statusvalue") Then statusvalue.Add(var.Value) Continue For End If If var.Value.ToString().Contains("SQLNCLI") Then orchestrationDBconnection = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("commandtimeoutval") Then commandtimeoutval = var.Value Continue For End If
Next
End Sub
Public Sub Main() ' ' Add your code here ' Dim apiname As String = "usp_get_process_run_info" Dim orchestrationschema As String = "" Dim myprocessname As String = "" Dim orchestrationDBconnection As String = "" Dim operationtype As String = "" Dim goodflag As Nullable(Of Integer) = Nothing Dim commandtimeoutval As Integer = 7200
Dim procReturn As Integer Dim runid As Nullable(Of Integer) = Nothing Dim status As String = "" Dim exceptionmsg As String = "" Dim eventid As Integer = 0 Dim taskname As String = "" Dim statusvalue As New List(Of String)
iterateInputvars(orchestrationschema, myprocessname, orchestrationDBconnection, operationtype, taskname, statusvalue, commandtimeoutval, goodflag)
If operationtype = "Manual" Or operationtype = "Exclude" Then Dts.TaskResult = ScriptResults.Success Return ElseIf operationtype = "Automatic" Then
' call function to call orchestration 'callOrch(orchestrationDBconnection, orchestrationschema, apiname, myprocessname, procReturn, status, runid) Try usp_get_process_run_info(orchestrationDBconnection, orchestrationschema, myprocessname, goodflag, procReturn, status, runid, exceptionmsg, eventid, commandtimeoutval)
Catch ex As Exception exceptionmsg = "Exception:" + ex.Message.ToString() End Try
If Not statusvalue.Contains(status) Then If exceptionmsg.Length > 0 Then exceptionmsg = exceptionmsg + "; " + status + " of " + myprocessname + " doesnt match expected status value" Else exceptionmsg = status + " status of " + myprocessname + " doesnt match expected status" End If eventid = -996 End If If procReturn <> 0 Then exceptionmsg = exceptionmsg + "; Orchestration returned Invalid returncode" End If Else exceptionmsg = "Invalid operationtype specified" eventid = -1 End If ' assign result to output vars iterateOutputvars(procReturn, runid, status)
' if there was an exception, eventid is not zero, status doesnt match expected status, or procReturn is not zero then fail task If exceptionmsg <> "" Or eventid <> 0 Or Not statusvalue.Contains(status) Or procReturn <> 0 Then Dim emptyBytes(0) As Byte Dts.Log("Exception msg:" & exceptionmsg, 0, emptyBytes) Dts.Events.FireError(eventid, taskname, exceptionmsg, String.Empty, 0) End If
Dts.TaskResult = ScriptResults.Success End Sub
Public Sub usp_get_process_run_info(ByVal orchestrationDBconnection As String, _ ByVal orchestrationschema As String, _ ByVal myprocessname As String, _ ByVal goodflag As Nullable(Of Integer), _ ByRef procReturn As Integer, _ ByRef status As String, _ ByRef runID As Nullable(Of Integer), _ ByRef exceptionmsg As String, _ ByRef eventid As Integer, _ Optional ByVal commandTimeoutVal As Integer = 7200) ' add connection info Dim apiname As String = "usp_get_process_run_info" Dim cn As New OleDb.OleDbConnection(orchestrationDBconnection)
Dim nonquerycommand As OleDb.OleDbCommand = cn.CreateCommand() nonquerycommand.CommandType = CommandType.StoredProcedure nonquerycommand.CommandTimeout = commandTimeoutVal
Try 'open connection cn.Open()
'create command text nonquerycommand.CommandText = orchestrationschema + "." + apiname
' add parameters Dim l_procreturn As New OleDb.OleDbParameter l_procreturn = nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.Integer, 8) l_procreturn.Direction = ParameterDirection.ReturnValue
nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 100).Value = myprocessname
Dim l_runid As New OleDb.OleDbParameter l_runid = nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.Integer, 8) l_runid.Direction = ParameterDirection.Output
Dim l_status As OleDb.OleDbParameter l_status = nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 100) l_status.Direction = ParameterDirection.Output
nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.Integer, 8).Value = goodflag
'prepare command for exec nonquerycommand.Prepare()
' call get info from Orchestration nonquerycommand.ExecuteNonQuery()
status = l_status.Value procReturn = l_procreturn.Value If Not IsDBNull(l_runid.Value) AndAlso Integer.TryParse(l_runid.Value, 0) Then runID = l_runid.Value 'Else : runID = 0 End If
Catch ex As OleDb.OleDbException procReturn = -1 status = "" runID = -1 eventid = -995 exceptionmsg = "OLEDB Exception: " + ex.Message.ToString() Catch ex As ArgumentException procReturn = -1 status = "" runID = -1 eventid = -994 exceptionmsg = "Argument Exception: " + ex.Message.ToString() Catch ex As Exception procReturn = -1 status = "" runID = -1 eventid = -1 exceptionmsg = ex.Message.ToString() Finally If cn.State = ConnectionState.Open Then cn.Close() End If
End Try
End Sub
End Class

Public Sub iterateOutputvars(ByRef procreturn As Integer, ByRef processreturnvalueint As Integer) For Each var In Dts.Variables If var.Name.Contains("procreturn") Then var.Value = procreturn Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("processreturnvalueint") Then var.Value = processreturnvalueint Continue For End If Next
End Sub Public Sub iterateInputvars(ByRef orchestrationschema As String, ByRef myprocessname As String, ByRef orchestrationDBconnection As String, ByRef datatypename As String, ByRef valuerolename As String, ByRef lowerbound As String, ByRef upperbound As String, ByRef taskname As String, ByRef operationtype As String, ByRef commandtimeoutval As Integer) For Each var In Dts.Variables If var.Name.Contains("schema") Then orchestrationschema = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("processname") Then myprocessname = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Value.ToString().Contains("SQLNCLI") Then orchestrationDBconnection = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("datatypename") Then datatypename = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("valuerolename") Then valuerolename = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("lowerbound") Then lowerbound = var.Value.ToString() Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("upperbound") Then upperbound = var.Value.ToString() Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("TaskName") Then taskname = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("operationtype") Then operationtype = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("commandtimeoutval") Then commandtimeoutval = var.Value Continue For End If
Next

Dim procReturn As Integer Dim processreturnvalueint As Integer Dim exceptionmsg As String = "" Dim eventid As Integer = 0 Dim taskname As String = ""
iterateInputvars(orchestrationschema, myprocessname, orchestrationDBconnection, datatypename, valuerolename, lowerbound, upperbound, taskname, operationtype, commandtimeoutval)

End If ' assign result to output vars iterateOutputvars(procReturn, processreturnvalueint)

Public Sub call_set_value(ByVal orchestrationDBconnection As String, ByVal orchestrationschema As String, ByVal myprocessname As String, ByVal datatypename As String, ByVal valuerolename As String, ByVal lowerbound As String, ByVal upperbound As String, ByRef procReturn As Integer, ByRef processreturnvalueint As Integer, ByRef exceptionmsg As String, ByRef eventid As Integer, Optional ByVal commandTimeoutVal As Integer = 7200) ' add connection info Dim apiname As String = "sp_SetValue" Dim cn As New OleDb.OleDbConnection(orchestrationDBconnection)
Dim nonquerycommand As OleDb.OleDbCommand = cn.CreateCommand() nonquerycommand.CommandType = CommandType.StoredProcedure nonquerycommand.CommandTimeout = commandTimeoutVal Try 'open connection cn.Open()
'create command text nonquerycommand.CommandText = orchestrationschema + "." + apiname
' add parameters Dim l_procreturn As New OleDb.OleDbParameter l_procreturn = nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.Integer, 8) l_procreturn.Direction = ParameterDirection.ReturnValue
nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 500).Value = datatypename nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 50).Value = valuerolename nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 200).Value = myprocessname nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 4000).Value = lowerbound If String.IsNullOrEmpty(upperbound) = False Then nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 4000).Value = upperbound Else nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 4000).Value = DBNull.Value End If
Dim l_processreturnvalueint As New OleDb.OleDbParameter l_processreturnvalueint = nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.Integer, 8) l_processreturnvalueint.Direction = ParameterDirection.Output
'prepare command for exec nonquerycommand.Prepare()
' call get info from Orchestration nonquerycommand.ExecuteNonQuery()
procReturn = l_procreturn.Value If Not IsDBNull(l_processreturnvalueint.Value) AndAlso Integer.TryParse(l_processreturnvalueint.Value, 0) Then processreturnvalueint = l_processreturnvalueint.Value Else : processreturnvalueint = -1 End If
Catch ex As OleDb.OleDbException procReturn = -1 processreturnvalueint = -1 eventid = -995 exceptionmsg = "OLEDB Exception: " + ex.Message.ToString() Catch ex As ArgumentException procReturn = -1 processreturnvalueint = -1 eventid = -994 exceptionmsg = "Argument Exception: " + ex.Message.ToString() Catch ex As InvalidCastException procReturn = -1 processreturnvalueint = -1 eventid = -993 exceptionmsg = "Invalid cast Exception: " + ex.Message.ToString() Catch ex As Exception procReturn = -1 processreturnvalueint = -1 eventid = -1 exceptionmsg = ex.Message.ToString() Finally If cn.State = ConnectionState.Open Then cn.Close() End If
End Try

' The execution engine calls this method when the task executes. ' To access the object model, use the Dts property. Connections, variables, events, ' and logging features are available as members of the Dts property as shown in the following examples. ' ' To reference a variable, call Dts.Variables("MyCaseSensitiveVariableName").Value ' To post a log entry, call Dts.Log("This is my log text", 999, Nothing) ' To fire an event, call Dts.Events.FireInformation(99, "test", "hit the help message", "", 0, True) ' ' To use the connections collection use something like the following: ' ConnectionManager cm = Dts.Connections.Add("OLEDB") ' cm.ConnectionString = "Data Source=localhost;Initial Catalog=AdventureWorks;Provider=SQLNCLI10;Integrated Security=SSPI;Auto Translate=False;" ' ' Before returning from this method, set the value of Dts.TaskResult to indicate success or failure. ' ' To open Help, press F1. Public Sub iterateOutputvars(ByRef procreturn As Integer, ByRef processreturnvalueint As Integer, ByRef statusexpvarname As String) For Each var In Dts.Variables If var.Name.Contains("procreturn") Then var.Value = procreturn Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("processreturnvalueint") Then var.Value = processreturnvalueint Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains(statusexpvarname) Then var.Value = "" Continue For End If Next
End Sub Public Sub iterateInputvars(ByRef orchestrationschema As String, ByRef myprocessname As String, ByRef orchestrationDBconnection As String, ByRef currentstatus As String, ByRef scopestartdate As Date, ByRef scopeenddate As Date, ByRef taskname As String, ByRef operationtype As String, ByRef commandtimeoutval As Integer, ByRef statusexplanation As String, ByRef statusexpvarname As String) For Each var In Dts.Variables If var.Name.Contains("schema") Then orchestrationschema = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("processname") Then myprocessname = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("scopestartdate") Then scopestartdate = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("scopeenddate") Then scopeenddate = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Value.ToString().Contains("SQLNCLI") Then orchestrationDBconnection = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("statusvalue") Then currentstatus = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("TaskName") Then taskname = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("operationtype") Then operationtype = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("commandtimeoutval") Then commandtimeoutval = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("statusexplanation") Then statusexpvarname = var.Name statusexplanation = var.Value Continue For End If
Next
End Sub
Public Sub Main() ' ' Add your code here ' Dim orchestrationschema As String = "" Dim myprocessname As String = "" Dim orchestrationDBconnection As String = "" Dim currentstatus As String = "" Dim scopestartdate As Date Dim scopeenddate As Date Dim procReturn As Integer Dim processreturnvalueint As Integer Dim exceptionmsg As String = "" Dim eventid As Integer = 0 Dim taskname As String = "" Dim operationtype As String = "" Dim commandtimeoutval As Integer = 7200 Dim statusexplanation As String = "" Dim statusexpvarname As String = ""
iterateInputvars(orchestrationschema, myprocessname, orchestrationDBconnection, currentstatus, scopestartdate, scopeenddate, taskname, operationtype, commandtimeoutval, statusexplanation, statusexpvarname)
If operationtype = "Manual" Or operationtype = "Exclude" Then Dts.TaskResult = ScriptResults.Success Return ElseIf operationtype = "Automatic" Then
' call function to call orchestration Try usp_set_status(orchestrationDBconnection, orchestrationschema, myprocessname, currentstatus, scopestartdate, scopeenddate, procReturn, processreturnvalueint, exceptionmsg, eventid, commandtimeoutval, statusexplanation) Catch ex As Exception exceptionmsg = "Exception:" + ex.Message.ToString() End Try If procReturn <> 0 Then exceptionmsg = exceptionmsg + "; Orchestration returned Invalid returncode" End If If processreturnvalueint <> 0 Then exceptionmsg = exceptionmsg + "; API call returned Invalid returncode" End If
Else exceptionmsg = "Invalid operationtype specified" eventid = -1
End If ' assign result to output vars iterateOutputvars(procReturn, processreturnvalueint, statusexpvarname)
' if there was an exception, eventid is not zero, status doesnt match expected status, or procReturn is not zero then fail task If exceptionmsg <> "" Or eventid <> 0 Or procReturn <> 0 Or processreturnvalueint <> 0 Then Dim emptyBytes(0) As Byte Dts.Log("Exception msg:" & exceptionmsg, 0, emptyBytes) Dts.Events.FireError(eventid, taskname, exceptionmsg, String.Empty, 0) End If Dts.TaskResult = ScriptResults.Success End Sub

Dim nonquerycommand As OleDb.OleDbCommand = cn.CreateCommand() nonquerycommand.CommandType = CommandType.StoredProcedure nonquerycommand.CommandTimeout = commandTimeoutVal
Dim l_statusexplanation As String If statusexplanation = "" Then l_statusexplanation = myprocessname + " is set to " + currentstatus Else l_statusexplanation = statusexplanation End If
Try 'open connection cn.Open()
'create command text nonquerycommand.CommandText = orchestrationschema + "." + apiname
' add parameters Dim l_procreturn As New OleDb.OleDbParameter l_procreturn = nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.Integer, 8) l_procreturn.Direction = ParameterDirection.ReturnValue
nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 100).Value = currentstatus nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 100).Value = myprocessname nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.DBDate, 10).Value = scopestartdate nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.DBDate, 10).Value = scopeenddate nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 4000).Value = l_statusexplanation
Dim l_processreturnvalueint As New OleDb.OleDbParameter l_processreturnvalueint = nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.Integer, 8) l_processreturnvalueint.Direction = ParameterDirection.Output
'prepare command for exec nonquerycommand.Prepare()
' call get info from Orchestration nonquerycommand.ExecuteNonQuery()
procReturn = l_procreturn.Value If Not IsDBNull(l_processreturnvalueint.Value) AndAlso Integer.TryParse(l_processreturnvalueint.Value, 0) Then processreturnvalueint = l_processreturnvalueint.Value Else : processreturnvalueint = -1 End If
Catch ex As OleDb.OleDbException procReturn = -1 processreturnvalueint = -1 eventid = -995 exceptionmsg = "OLEDB Exception: " + ex.Message.ToString() Catch ex As ArgumentException procReturn = -1 processreturnvalueint = -1 eventid = -994 exceptionmsg = "Argument Exception: " + ex.Message.ToString() Catch ex As InvalidCastException procReturn = -1 processreturnvalueint = -1 eventid = -993 exceptionmsg = "Invalid cast Exception: " + ex.Message.ToString() Catch ex As Exception procReturn = -1 processreturnvalueint = -1 eventid = -1 exceptionmsg = ex.Message.ToString() Finally If cn.State = ConnectionState.Open Then cn.Close() End If
End Try End Sub
End Class

Public Sub usp_get_process_run_info(ByVal orchestrationDBconnection As String, _ ByVal orchestrationschema As String, _ ByVal myprocessname As String, _ ByVal goodflag As Nullable(Of Integer), _ ByRef procReturn As Integer, _ ByRef status As String, _ ByRef runID As Nullable(Of Integer), _ ByRef exceptionmsg As String, _ ByRef eventid As Integer, _ Optional ByVal commandTimeoutVal As Integer = 7200) ' add connection info Dim apiname As String = "usp_get_process_run_info" Dim cn As New OleDb.OleDbConnection(orchestrationDBconnection)
Dim nonquerycommand As OleDb.OleDbCommand = cn.CreateCommand() nonquerycommand.CommandType = CommandType.StoredProcedure nonquerycommand.CommandTimeout = commandTimeoutVal
Try 'open connection cn.Open()
'create command text nonquerycommand.CommandText = orchestrationschema + "." + apiname
' add parameters Dim l_procreturn As New OleDb.OleDbParameter l_procreturn = nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.Integer, 8) l_procreturn.Direction = ParameterDirection.ReturnValue
nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 100).Value = myprocessname
Dim l_runid As New OleDb.OleDbParameter l_runid = nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.Integer, 8) l_runid.Direction = ParameterDirection.Output
Dim l_status As OleDb.OleDbParameter l_status = nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 100) l_status.Direction = ParameterDirection.Output
nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.Integer, 8).Value = goodflag
'prepare command for exec nonquerycommand.Prepare()
' call get info from Orchestration nonquerycommand.ExecuteNonQuery()
status = l_status.Value procReturn = l_procreturn.Value If Not IsDBNull(l_runid.Value) AndAlso Integer.TryParse(l_runid.Value, 0) Then runID = l_runid.Value 'Else : runID = 0 End If
Catch ex As OleDb.OleDbException procReturn = -1 status = "" runID = -1 eventid = -995 exceptionmsg = "OLEDB Exception: " + ex.Message.ToString() Catch ex As ArgumentException procReturn = -1 status = "" runID = -1 eventid = -994 exceptionmsg = "Argument Exception: " + ex.Message.ToString() Catch ex As Exception procReturn = -1 status = "" runID = -1 eventid = -1 exceptionmsg = ex.Message.ToString() Finally If cn.State = ConnectionState.Open Then cn.Close() End If

Public Sub iterateOutputvars(ByRef procreturn As Integer, ByRef processreturnvalueint As Integer, ByRef statusexpvarname As String) For Each var In Dts.Variables If var.Name.Contains("procreturn") Then var.Value = procreturn Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("processreturnvalueint") Then var.Value = processreturnvalueint Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains(statusexpvarname) Then var.Value = "" Continue For End If Next
End Sub Public Sub iterateInputvars(ByRef orchestrationschema As String, ByRef myprocessname As String, ByRef orchestrationDBconnection As String, ByRef currentstatus As String, ByRef scopestartdate As Date, ByRef scopeenddate As Date, ByRef taskname As String, ByRef operationtype As String, ByRef commandtimeoutval As Integer, ByRef statusexplanation As String, ByRef statusexpvarname As String) For Each var In Dts.Variables If var.Name.Contains("schema") Then orchestrationschema = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("processname") Then myprocessname = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("scopestartdate") Then scopestartdate = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("scopeenddate") Then scopeenddate = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Value.ToString().Contains("SQLNCLI") Then orchestrationDBconnection = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("statusvalue") Then currentstatus = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("TaskName") Then taskname = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("operationtype") Then operationtype = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("commandtimeoutval") Then commandtimeoutval = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("statusexplanation") Then statusexpvarname = var.Name statusexplanation = var.Value Continue For End If
Next

Public Sub Main() ' ' Add your code here ' Dim orchestrationschema As String = "" Dim myprocessname As String = "" Dim orchestrationDBconnection As String = "" Dim currentstatus As String = "" Dim scopestartdate As Date Dim scopeenddate As Date Dim procReturn As Integer Dim processreturnvalueint As Integer Dim exceptionmsg As String = "" Dim eventid As Integer = 0 Dim taskname As String = "" Dim operationtype As String = "" Dim commandtimeoutval As Integer = 7200 Dim statusexplanation As String = "" Dim statusexpvarname As String = ""
iterateInputvars(orchestrationschema, myprocessname, orchestrationDBconnection, currentstatus, scopestartdate, scopeenddate, taskname, operationtype, commandtimeoutval, statusexplanation, statusexpvarname)
If operationtype = "Manual" Or operationtype = "Exclude" Then Dts.TaskResult = ScriptResults.Success Return ElseIf operationtype = "Automatic" Then
' call function to call orchestration Try usp_set_status(orchestrationDBconnection, orchestrationschema, myprocessname, currentstatus, scopestartdate, scopeenddate, procReturn, processreturnvalueint, exceptionmsg, eventid, commandtimeoutval, statusexplanation) Catch ex As Exception exceptionmsg = "Exception:" + ex.Message.ToString() End Try If procReturn <> 0 Then exceptionmsg = exceptionmsg + "; Orchestration returned Invalid returncode" End If If processreturnvalueint <> 0 Then exceptionmsg = exceptionmsg + "; API call returned Invalid returncode" End If
Else exceptionmsg = "Invalid operationtype specified" eventid = -1
End If ' assign result to output vars iterateOutputvars(procReturn, processreturnvalueint, statusexpvarname)
' if there was an exception, eventid is not zero, status doesnt match expected status, or procReturn is not zero then fail task If exceptionmsg <> "" Or eventid <> 0 Or procReturn <> 0 Or processreturnvalueint <> 0 Then Dim emptyBytes(0) As Byte Dts.Log("Exception msg:" & exceptionmsg, 0, emptyBytes) Dts.Events.FireError(eventid, taskname, exceptionmsg, String.Empty, 0) End If Dts.TaskResult = ScriptResults.Success End Sub
Public Sub usp_set_status(ByVal orchestrationDBconnection As String, _ ByVal orchestrationschema As String, _ ByVal myprocessname As String, _ ByVal currentstatus As String, _ ByRef scopestartdate As Date, _ ByRef scopeenddate As Date, _ ByRef procReturn As Integer, _ ByRef processreturnvalueint As Integer, _ ByRef exceptionmsg As String, _ ByRef eventid As Integer, _ Optional ByVal commandTimeoutVal As Integer = 7200, _ Optional ByVal statusexplanation As String = "") ' add connection info Dim apiname As String = "sp_SetStatus" Dim cn As New OleDb.OleDbConnection(orchestrationDBconnection)
Dim nonquerycommand As OleDb.OleDbCommand = cn.CreateCommand() nonquerycommand.CommandType = CommandType.StoredProcedure nonquerycommand.CommandTimeout = commandTimeoutVal
Dim l_statusexplanation As String If statusexplanation = "" Then l_statusexplanation = myprocessname + " is set to " + currentstatus Else l_statusexplanation = statusexplanation End If
Try 'open connection cn.Open()
'create command text nonquerycommand.CommandText = orchestrationschema + "." + apiname
' add parameters Dim l_procreturn As New OleDb.OleDbParameter l_procreturn = nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.Integer, 8) l_procreturn.Direction = ParameterDirection.ReturnValue
nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 100).Value = currentstatus nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 100).Value = myprocessname nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.DBDate, 10).Value = scopestartdate nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.DBDate, 10).Value = scopeenddate nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 4000).Value = l_statusexplanation
Dim l_processreturnvalueint As New OleDb.OleDbParameter l_processreturnvalueint = nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.Integer, 8) l_processreturnvalueint.Direction = ParameterDirection.Output
'prepare command for exec nonquerycommand.Prepare()
' call get info from Orchestration nonquerycommand.ExecuteNonQuery()
procReturn = l_procreturn.Value If Not IsDBNull(l_processreturnvalueint.Value) AndAlso Integer.TryParse(l_processreturnvalueint.Value, 0) Then processreturnvalueint = l_processreturnvalueint.Value Else : processreturnvalueint = -1 End If
Catch ex As OleDb.OleDbException procReturn = -1 processreturnvalueint = -1 eventid = -995 exceptionmsg = "OLEDB Exception: " + ex.Message.ToString() Catch ex As ArgumentException procReturn = -1 processreturnvalueint = -1 eventid = -994 exceptionmsg = "Argument Exception: " + ex.Message.ToString() Catch ex As InvalidCastException procReturn = -1 processreturnvalueint = -1 eventid = -993 exceptionmsg = "Invalid cast Exception: " + ex.Message.ToString() Catch ex As Exception procReturn = -1 processreturnvalueint = -1 eventid = -1 exceptionmsg = ex.Message.ToString() Finally If cn.State = ConnectionState.Open Then cn.Close() End If
End Try End Sub

Enum ScriptResults Success = Microsoft.SqlServer.Dts.Runtime.DTSExecResult.Success Failure = Microsoft.SqlServer.Dts.Runtime.DTSExecResult.Failure End Enum
' The execution engine calls this method when the task executes. ' To access the object model, use the Dts property. Connections, variables, events, ' and logging features are available as members of the Dts property as shown in the following examples. ' ' To reference a variable, call Dts.Variables("MyCaseSensitiveVariableName").Value ' To post a log entry, call Dts.Log("This is my log text", 999, Nothing) ' To fire an event, call Dts.Events.FireInformation(99, "test", "hit the help message", "", 0, True) ' ' To use the connections collection use something like the following: ' ConnectionManager cm = Dts.Connections.Add("OLEDB") ' cm.ConnectionString = "Data Source=localhost;Initial Catalog=AdventureWorks;Provider=SQLNCLI10;Integrated Security=SSPI;Auto Translate=False;" ' ' Before returning from this method, set the value of Dts.TaskResult to indicate success or failure. ' ' To open Help, press F1. Public Sub iterateOutputvars(ByRef procreturn As Integer, ByRef processreturnvalueint As Integer, ByRef statusexpvarname As String) For Each var In Dts.Variables If var.Name.Contains("procreturn") Then var.Value = procreturn Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("processreturnvalueint") Then var.Value = processreturnvalueint Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains(statusexpvarname) Then var.Value = "" Continue For End If Next
End Sub Public Sub iterateInputvars(ByRef orchestrationschema As String, ByRef myprocessname As String, ByRef orchestrationDBconnection As String, ByRef currentstatus As String, ByRef scopestartdate As Date, ByRef scopeenddate As Date, ByRef taskname As String, ByRef operationtype As String, ByRef commandtimeoutval As Integer, ByRef statusexplanation As String, ByRef statusexpvarname As String) For Each var In Dts.Variables If var.Name.Contains("schema") Then orchestrationschema = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("processname") Then myprocessname = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("scopestartdate") Then scopestartdate = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("scopeenddate") Then scopeenddate = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Value.ToString().Contains("SQLNCLI") Then orchestrationDBconnection = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("statusvalue") Then currentstatus = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("TaskName") Then taskname = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("operationtype") Then operationtype = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("commandtimeoutval") Then commandtimeoutval = var.Value Continue For End If If var.Name.Contains("statusexplanation") Then statusexpvarname = var.Name statusexplanation = var.Value Continue For End If
Next
End Sub
Public Sub Main() ' ' Add your code here ' Dim orchestrationschema As String = "" Dim myprocessname As String = "" Dim orchestrationDBconnection As String = "" Dim currentstatus As String = "" Dim scopestartdate As Date Dim scopeenddate As Date Dim procReturn As Integer Dim processreturnvalueint As Integer Dim exceptionmsg As String = "" Dim eventid As Integer = 0 Dim taskname As String = "" Dim operationtype As String = "" Dim commandtimeoutval As Integer = 7200 Dim statusexplanation As String = "" Dim statusexpvarname As String = ""
iterateInputvars(orchestrationschema, myprocessname, orchestrationDBconnection, currentstatus, scopestartdate, scopeenddate, taskname, operationtype, commandtimeoutval, statusexplanation, statusexpvarname)
If operationtype = "Manual" Or operationtype = "Exclude" Then Dts.TaskResult = ScriptResults.Success Return ElseIf operationtype = "Automatic" Then
' call function to call orchestration Try usp_set_status(orchestrationDBconnection, orchestrationschema, myprocessname, currentstatus, scopestartdate, scopeenddate, procReturn, processreturnvalueint, exceptionmsg, eventid, commandtimeoutval, statusexplanation) Catch ex As Exception exceptionmsg = "Exception:" + ex.Message.ToString() End Try If procReturn <> 0 Then exceptionmsg = exceptionmsg + "; Orchestration returned Invalid returncode" End If If processreturnvalueint <> 0 Then exceptionmsg = exceptionmsg + "; API call returned Invalid returncode" End If
Else exceptionmsg = "Invalid operationtype specified" eventid = -1
End If ' assign result to output vars iterateOutputvars(procReturn, processreturnvalueint, statusexpvarname)
' if there was an exception, eventid is not zero, status doesnt match expected status, or procReturn is not zero then fail task If exceptionmsg <> "" Or eventid <> 0 Or procReturn <> 0 Or processreturnvalueint <> 0 Then Dim emptyBytes(0) As Byte Dts.Log("Exception msg:" & exceptionmsg, 0, emptyBytes) Dts.Events.FireError(eventid, taskname, exceptionmsg, String.Empty, 0) End If Dts.TaskResult = ScriptResults.Success End Sub
Public Sub usp_set_status(ByVal orchestrationDBconnection As String, _ ByVal orchestrationschema As String, _ ByVal myprocessname As String, _ ByVal currentstatus As String, _ ByRef scopestartdate As Date, _ ByRef scopeenddate As Date, _ ByRef procReturn As Integer, _ ByRef processreturnvalueint As Integer, _ ByRef exceptionmsg As String, _ ByRef eventid As Integer, _ Optional ByVal commandTimeoutVal As Integer = 7200, _ Optional ByVal statusexplanation As String = "") ' add connection info Dim apiname As String = "sp_SetStatus" Dim cn As New OleDb.OleDbConnection(orchestrationDBconnection)
Dim nonquerycommand As OleDb.OleDbCommand = cn.CreateCommand() nonquerycommand.CommandType = CommandType.StoredProcedure nonquerycommand.CommandTimeout = commandTimeoutVal
Dim l_statusexplanation As String If statusexplanation = "" Then l_statusexplanation = myprocessname + " is set to " + currentstatus Else l_statusexplanation = statusexplanation End If
Try 'open connection cn.Open()
'create command text nonquerycommand.CommandText = orchestrationschema + "." + apiname
' add parameters Dim l_procreturn As New OleDb.OleDbParameter l_procreturn = nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.Integer, 8) l_procreturn.Direction = ParameterDirection.ReturnValue
nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 100).Value = currentstatus nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 100).Value = myprocessname nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.DBDate, 10).Value = scopestartdate nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.DBDate, 10).Value = scopeenddate nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.VarChar, 4000).Value = l_statusexplanation
Dim l_processreturnvalueint As New OleDb.OleDbParameter l_processreturnvalueint = nonquerycommand.Parameters.Add("?", OleDb.OleDbType.Integer, 8) l_processreturnvalueint.Direction = ParameterDirection.Output
'prepare command for exec nonquerycommand.Prepare()
' call get info from Orchestration nonquerycommand.ExecuteNonQuery()
procReturn = l_procreturn.Value If Not IsDBNull(l_processreturnvalueint.Value) AndAlso Integer.TryParse(l_processreturnvalueint.Value, 0) Then processreturnvalueint = l_processreturnvalueint.Value Else : processreturnvalueint = -1 End If
Catch ex As OleDb.OleDbException procReturn = -1 processreturnvalueint = -1 eventid = -995 exceptionmsg = "OLEDB Exception: " + ex.Message.ToString() Catch ex As ArgumentException procReturn = -1 processreturnvalueint = -1 eventid = -994 exceptionmsg = "Argument Exception: " + ex.Message.ToString() Catch ex As InvalidCastException procReturn = -1 processreturnvalueint = -1 eventid = -993 exceptionmsg = "Invalid cast Exception: " + ex.Message.ToString() Catch ex As Exception procReturn = -1 processreturnvalueint = -1 eventid = -1 exceptionmsg = ex.Message.ToString() Finally If cn.State = ConnectionState.Open Then cn.Close() End If
End Try End Sub
End Class
